# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in your own Google OAuth Client ID.
#
# How to get one (takes ~5 minutes):
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/  and create a project.
#   2. APIs & Services > Library > enable "Gmail API".
#   3. APIs & Services > OAuth consent screen:
#        - User type: External
#        - Add your Google account under "Test users" (required while app is in Testing).
#        - Add scope: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.modify
#   4. APIs & Services > Credentials > Create credentials > OAuth client ID:
#        - Application type: Web application
#        - Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:5173
#          (add your production URL here too when you deploy)
#   5. Copy the generated Client ID below.
#
# Deploying (e.g. Vercel):
#   - Set VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID in the host's dashboard env vars, NOT in a
#     committed file. Vite inlines it at build time, so redeploy after changing it.
#   - Add your production origin (e.g. https://<app>.vercel.app) to the OAuth
#     client's "Authorized JavaScript origins" — exact, https, no trailing slash.
#   - Per-push preview URLs won't work for OAuth (Google has no wildcard origins);
#     sign in on the stable Production / custom domain.

VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here.apps.googleusercontent.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google AdSense (optional — for ad revenue)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Your AdSense publisher ID. Leave blank to disable ads entirely (no script
# loads, <AdSlot> renders nothing). Create ad units in the AdSense dashboard
# and put their slot IDs in the <AdSlot slot="..."> props (Login + Dashboard).
# NOTE: AdSense + Gmail API policy forbid ads next to private email content —
# keep ads on public/overview surfaces only.
VITE_ADSENSE_CLIENT=ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# User tracking + admin list (server-side; Vercel only)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The app records each signed-in account's email so you can see who used it.
#   - Storage: a Vercel KV store (private Redis). In the Vercel dashboard:
#       Storage > Create > KV, then connect it to this project. That auto-injects
#       KV_REST_API_URL and KV_REST_API_TOKEN — you do NOT set those by hand, and
#       you must NOT put them in this committed file.
#   - The list lives in KV, so deploys/rebuilds never clear it.
#
# Admin password: NO env var needed. The password is stored hashed (SHA-256)
# directly in code (src/components/AdminUserList.tsx and api/users.ts), so there
# is nothing to configure here. To change it, replace the hash in both files.
# View the list at:  https://<your-app>/user-list   (enter the password)
# Or download:       https://<your-app>/api/users?token=<password>
